# 🗄 Core Database Tables

### Users

* id
* name
* email
* password_hash
* role
* created_at

### Accounts

* id
* user_id
* account_number
* balance
* status
* created_at

### Transactions

* id
* from_account_id
* to_account_id
* amount
* type
* status
* reference_id
* created_at

### Loans

* id
* user_id
* amount
* interest_rate
* emi_amount
* status

---

# 📈 Scalability Strategy

* Stateless backend services
* Load balancer support
* Database primary + read replicas
* Redis caching (carefully for balance reads)
* Event-driven notifications
* Dead-letter queues for failed events
* CDN for frontend assets

---

# 🧪 Testing Strategy

## Backend

* Unit testing (Jest)
* Integration testing
* Transaction consistency testing
* Load testing for transfer operations

## Frontend

* Component testing
* API integration testing
* End-to-end testing (Cypress / Playwright)

